                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Baron de Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 536.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to the conversations which I
                    have had the honor to hold with you, and with especial preference to your
                    excellency’s letter of the 2d of December, I regret to inform you that after
                    mature deliberation and a careful examination of all the circumstances in the
                    case, this Government thinks it not expedient to reconsider the decision already
                    arrived at for the discontinuance of the Italian bureau at the New York
                    immigration station.</p>
                <p>With the highest regard, I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
